<p>Eugene O\'Neill\'s Pulitzer Prize-winning drama Anna Christie tells the story of a young woman’s struggle for redemption and a chance at a new life. Harboring a troubling secret from her past, Anna reunites with her father - a captain, a master of the sea, and a man she hardly knows. As the wild and dangerous waters would have it, Anna meets a shipwrecked young sailor and the two fall in love. When she finds she can no longer hide her past from the two men in her life, the bonds of love are tested. A powerful and relevant retelling of O\'Neill\'s masterpiece, the play continues to challenge our understanding of honor and dignity.</p>
